# System Prompting

#### There are two more strategies you can use when writing system prompts: **chain of reasoning** and **giving examples**.


## Chain of Reasoning
#### The steps the model takes to explain its answer, showing how it got from the question to the final response, like solving a math problem step by step.
#### *Having trouble viewing the image or want more information, check out the relevant <a href='https://studio.code.org/s/exploring-gen-ai2-2025/lessons/5/levels/1?section_id=709' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>curriculum level</a>.*
<img src="https://images.code.org/b47dd24b89e67d4dbb150d1bf6298daf-Screenshot 2024-09-11 at 2.17.19 PM.png" alt="chain of reasoning example" width="900px" style="border: 2px solid black; border-radius: 8px; float:center">

<br>

## Giving Examples

#### Providing specific instances or situations to make the explanation clearer, like saying, "For example, when you..." to help people understand better.
#### *Having trouble viewing the image or want more information, check out the relevant <a href='https://studio.code.org/s/exploring-gen-ai2-2025/lessons/5/levels/5?section_id=709' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>curriculum level</a>.*
<img src="https://images.code.org/3432fa7472cb8abd54d4d89209b701fc-Screenshot 2024-09-11 at 2.18.21 PM.png" alt="giving examples example" width="900px" style="border: 2px solid black; border-radius: 8px; float:center">

<br>

## Up Next!
#### The next level is a **Choice Level** from the curriculum. Choice levels offer a chance to differentiate learning - in this one you'll choose between different scenarios to apply your system prompting skills. 

#### When you're trying out this level, remember the system prompting strategies we've discussed already - **role, tone, audience, and delivery** - as well as **chain of reasoning and giving examples**. Feel free to come back to this level if you get stuck.

<br>



